  <title>Working with the Problems View</title>
  <section id="the-problems-view">
    <title>The Problems View</title>
    <anchor role="helpid" id="problemViewContextId">Problem View</anchor>
    <para>
      The Problems View (<xref linkend="probview"/>) is in the middle of the specification perspective,
      at the bottom, by default.
    </para>
    <para>
      It shows three types of message:
    </para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <mediaobject role="icon" file="../images/info.png"/> Information
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <mediaobject role="icon" file="../images/error.png"/> Errors
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <mediaobject role="icon" file="../images/warning.png"/> Warnings
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <para>
      Right-clicking on a message and selecting <emphasis>Quick
      Fix</emphasis> will either solve the problem or take you to the
      place where you can solve the problem, if this is possible.
    </para>
    <figure id="probview">
      <title>Problems View</title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/probview.png"/>
        </imageobject>
        <textobject><phrase>Problems View</phrase></textobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
  </section>
</section>